        </title></titleInfo><titleInfo lang="en" type="translated"><title>Hymns for the Rite Involving Intonation of the Buddha’s Name According to the Five Tempos of the Pure Land</title></titleInfo><titleInfo type="reference"><title>T#1983, 47</title></titleInfo><abstract/><name xmlns:ns2="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" type="personal" ns2:href="#fazhao"><namePart lang="zh">法照</namePart><namePart transliteration="pinyin">Fazhao</namePart><namePart type="date">?-777</namePart><role><roleTerm>author</roleTerm></role></name><physicalDescription><extent><detail type="fascicle">1</detail></extent></physicalDescription><originInfo><dateOther>around 774</dateOther></originInfo><abstract>Title translated by Stevenson 2008, 163: Authored in Chang’an around 774 C.E., and later redacted by Fazhao into “expanded” and “abbreviated” versions, Fazhao’s ritual text[s] were used for seasonal cycles of Pure Land ritual worship in imperially appointed monasteries of Chang’an and outlying provinces (including Taiyuan and Mount Wutai in northern Shanxi province) between the mid-eighth and ninth centuries. As a young monk, Fazhao was exposed to a mix of Chan, Tiantai and emergent Pure Land teaching during his travels through Sichuan and Hunan provinces.... see Lopez 1996, Religions of China in Practice, here article by Stevenson.</abstract><relatedItem xmlns:ns2="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" ns2:href="Taisho" type="host"><titleInfo lang="ja"><title>大正新脩大藏經.</title></titleInfo><titleInfo transliteration="romaji"><title>Taishō shinshū daizōkyō</title></titleInfo><titleInfo type="abbreviated" transliteration="romaji"><title>Taishō</title></titleInfo><titleInfo type="translated" lang="en"><title>New edition of the Buddhist canon in the Taishō era</title></titleInfo><name type="personal" ns2:href="#takakusu"><namePart type="family" lang="ja">高楠</namePart><namePart type="given" lang="ja">順次郎</namePart><role><roleTerm>editor</roleTerm></role></name><name type="personal" ns2:href="#watanabe"><namePart type="family" lang="ja">渡邊</namePart><namePart type="given" lang="ja">海旭</namePart><role><roleTerm>editor</roleTerm></role></name><physicalDescription><extent><detail type="volume">85</detail></extent></physicalDescription><originInfo><dateIssued>1924-1932</dateIssued><dateIssued encoding="marc" point="start">1924</dateIssued><dateIssued encoding="marc" point="end">1932</dateIssued><place><placeTerm>Tōkyō</placeTerm></place><publisher><name type="corporate"><namePart lang="ja">大正一切經刊行會</namePart><namePart transliteration="pinyin">Taishō issaikyō kankōkai</namePart></name></publisher></originInfo><part><detail type="volume"><number>47</number></detail><extent unit="page"><start>474c</start><end>490c</end></extent></part></relatedItem></mods>